702511f.title: Brooklyn: 10th Street - Wythe Avenue
702511f.text:
South 10th Street, at, and adjoining the N. W. corner
of Wythe Avenue, showing two old frame houses. The colonnade ie
in the Corinthian order of classical Greek architecture, this type
of decorative dwellirnghaving been popular here in the latter part
of the nineteenth century.
1923
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
